        <h2 class="project-details-title">About the Turtle Shelter Project</h2>
        <div class="project-details-content">
          <p>
            One winter, when Jen was homeless, 7 of her friends froze to death. Jen is no longer
            homeless and has figured out a solution for those who don't have shelter against the cold: 
            High-tech foam vests that are inexpensive and keep a person warm up to 10 degrees below zero.
            These vests help save lives and alleviate suffering. You can enlist the help of your friends,
            family, community, business colleagues, church members, and clubs to help make these vests! 
            We provide all of the materials, you provide the space, then we work together to create a portable,
            lifesaving shelter for those in need.
          </p>
        </div>
          <br>
        <h2 class="project-details-title">Our Tech</h2>
        <div class="project-details-content">
          <p>
            Foam clothing, invented by outdoor survival expert Jim Phillips, uses open-cell polyurethane
            foam as insulation in jackets, pants, gloves, sleeping bags, and more. When paired with synthetic 
            fabrics, these vests provide breathable, moisture-wicking protection--ensuring body heat retention 
            even in freezing, wet conditions.
            <br>
            <br>
            Originally marketed for emergency preparedness and extreme sports, foam clothing is often 
            expensive. At Turtle Shelter, we make this technology accessible to those who need it most.
            These vests are like a turtle's shell: a portable, lifesaving shelter.
          </p>
